WEBVTT

00:01.101 --> 00:02.762
<i>Previously on "Heartland"...</i>

00:02.902 --> 00:04.233
Lou, this is Mackenzie Hutton.

00:04.371 --> 00:05.861
I'm not on a diet.
I'm allergic.

00:06.006 --> 00:06.734
Allergic to what?

00:06.873 --> 00:08.534
Dairy, white sugar,
seafood, gluten.

00:09.075 --> 00:11.066
Ow. There's mosquitoes!

00:11.211 --> 00:12.872
I'd rather marry
my real-estate broker

00:12.979 --> 00:14.571
than be with the moron
that you've wasted

00:14.714 --> 00:15.681
your last five years with.

00:15.782 --> 00:18.342
How we doing tonight?
Not interrupting anything, am I?

00:21.187 --> 00:22.415
My bodyguard has the night off.

00:22.522 --> 00:24.786
I don't know what Mindy told you,

00:24.958 --> 00:26.755
but whatever it was,
it isn't true.

00:26.860 --> 00:27.952
I don't know why it matters.

00:28.061 --> 00:29.892
I mean, everyone knows
you're with Kit.

00:30.864 --> 00:34.391
Where's the nearest
gluten-free bakery?

00:40.473 --> 00:42.805
Hey. Did you get
the gluten-free bread?

00:42.909 --> 00:44.035
I did.

00:44.177 --> 00:46.270
And the all-natural spring water?

00:46.379 --> 00:49.644
Yes. Mackenzie will be able
to take in food and water.

00:49.749 --> 00:51.740
This time, I am prepared
for all of her neuroses.

00:51.851 --> 00:54.649
Man, you know, I can't believe
she's marrying that real-estate guy.

00:54.754 --> 00:56.813
- She's not.
- Excuse me?

00:56.956 --> 00:58.321
She broke up with him.

00:58.491 --> 01:01.460
Oh. And she's engaged to someone
else since she's been here?

01:01.561 --> 01:04.724
Yeah, I know. Pretty fast.

01:04.831 --> 01:06.196
You know,
I don't know how anyone

01:06.299 --> 01:07.857
could live happily ever after
with her.

01:07.967 --> 01:10.629
- She is not all bad.
- Uh-huh.

01:10.737 --> 01:12.637
Okay, she's a nightmare.

01:12.739 --> 01:13.967
But she wants to get married here,

01:14.074 --> 01:16.235
and I am not about
to turn away her business.

01:16.342 --> 01:17.775
Besides, I'm happy for her.

01:18.878 --> 01:21.403
I mean it!

01:21.514 --> 01:24.039
Okay, so, maybe I don't mean it.

01:24.150 --> 01:25.515
Excuse me if I'm a little bit jaded,

01:25.685 --> 01:27.676
but the idea of planning
a Heartland wedding

01:27.787 --> 01:32.224
and building a little love nest
right now makes me want to barf.

01:32.325 --> 01:34.384
How does it look?

01:40.967 --> 01:42.992
She sure is something.

01:43.103 --> 01:44.832
An Andalusian.

01:52.145 --> 01:55.512
Well, Amy, here she is
in all her glory.

01:55.615 --> 01:57.048
Hello. How you doing, girl?

01:57.150 --> 01:59.675
Oh, be careful.
She has been known to bite.

01:59.786 --> 02:01.219
She's beautiful.

02:01.321 --> 02:03.516
Yep, she's beautiful, all right.

02:03.623 --> 02:05.284
People fall for her immediately.

02:05.391 --> 02:07.382
And then as soon as someone
buys her, they return her.

02:07.494 --> 02:09.051
This is her third return.

02:09.162 --> 02:11.392
Why do they bring her back?
What's wrong with her?

02:11.498 --> 02:14.331
Oh, she's cursed.

02:14.434 --> 02:16.459
So, why cursed?

02:16.569 --> 02:18.901
My husband Dan and I bought her
when she was a yearling.

02:19.005 --> 02:21.701
And, I swear, that horse
is one of the main reasons

02:21.808 --> 02:23.207
why he is now my ex-husband.

02:23.309 --> 02:25.243
Just coping with the animal

02:25.345 --> 02:27.973
was the last straw
that ruined my marriage.

02:28.081 --> 02:31.346
We called her Diva Girl,
the divorce horse.

02:31.451 --> 02:33.146
I'm not kidding.
I mean it.

02:33.253 --> 02:35.653
Whoever's on her
has ended up in divorce court.

02:35.755 --> 02:37.484
I think she's cursed.

02:37.590 --> 02:40.582
Luckily, I don't need a cursed horse
to ruin my relationships.

02:40.693 --> 02:42.593
I do that just fine on my own.

02:42.695 --> 02:44.390
Oh.

02:44.497 --> 02:46.727
Well, here comes the bride.

02:46.833 --> 02:48.027
Did you have a good trip?

02:48.168 --> 02:50.295
Yeah, the usual craziness.

02:50.403 --> 02:51.995
Lan missed his flight.

02:52.105 --> 02:54.437
His cab got in an accident
on the way to LaGuardia.

02:54.541 --> 02:56.099
Oh, no. Is he okay?

02:56.209 --> 02:58.234
Yeah, yeah. He's fine.
No worries.

02:58.378 --> 03:01.973
All right, well, hey, let me
just help you with your luggage

03:02.081 --> 03:04.606
Oh, no bags.
They lost all of them.

03:05.385 --> 03:06.181
No!

03:06.286 --> 03:09.221
Yep. Including the one
with my wedding dress in it.

03:09.322 --> 03:13.224
Oh, well, you know what?
You're here.

03:13.326 --> 03:14.691
So we're in good shape, right?

03:14.794 --> 03:16.125
Yeah, whatever. I'm fine.

03:16.229 --> 03:17.787
Really?

03:20.967 --> 03:21.865
Amy.

03:22.035 --> 03:24.196
Oh, my God,
what a beautiful horse.

03:24.304 --> 03:26.534
Careful.
Apparently, she bites.

03:26.639 --> 03:29.199
No, he likes me.

03:29.309 --> 03:30.867
That is so cute.

03:31.010 --> 03:32.272
She. It's a girl.

03:32.378 --> 03:35.176
That horse can smell a wedding
a mile away.

03:35.281 --> 03:37.408
It's the curse at work already.

